+@deffn {Interface Driver} {ch341a}
+This driver is implementing synchronous bitbang mode of an WCH CH341A,
+CH341H and similar USB Parallel/SPI bridge ICs by reusing UIO signals as GPIO.
+
+List of connections (default physical pin numbers for CH341A in 28-pin SOP package):
+@itemize @minus
+@item D3(18) - TCK
+@item D0(15) - TMS
+@item D7(22) - TDI
+@item D5(20) - TDO
+@item D1(16) - TRST
+@item D2(17) - SRST
+@end itemize
+
+List of connections (default physical pin numbers for CH341H in 20-pin SSOP package):
+@itemize @minus
+@item DCK(13) - TCK
+@item CS0(10) - TMS
+@item DIN(17) - TDI
+@item DOUT(15) - TDO
+@item CS1(11) - TRST
+@item CS2(12) - SRST
+@end itemize
+
+These interfaces have several commands, used to configure the driver
+before initializing the JTAG scan chain:
+
+@deffn {Config Command} {ch341a vid_pid} @var{vid} @var{pid}
+The vendor ID and product ID of the adapter. If not specified, default
+0x1a86:0x5512 is used.
+@end deffn
+
+@deffn {Config Command} {ch341a jtag_nums} @var{tck} @var{tms} @var{tdi} @var{tdo} @var{trst} @var{srst}
+Set four JTAG GPIO numbers at once.
+If not specified, default D3 D0 D7 D5 D1 D2 is used.
+@end deffn
+
+@deffn {Config Command} {ch341a tck_num} @var{tck}
+Set TCK GPIO number. If not specified, default D3 is used.
+@end deffn
+
+@deffn {Config Command} {ch341a tms_num} @var{tms}
+Set TMS GPIO number. If not specified, default D0 is used.
+@end deffn
+
+@deffn {Config Command} {ch341a tdi_num} @var{tdi}
+Set TDI GPIO number. If not specified, default D7 is used.
+@end deffn
+
+@deffn {Config Command} {ch341a tdo_num} @var{tdo}
+Set TDO GPIO number. If not specified, default D5 is used.
+@end deffn
+
+@deffn {Config Command} {ch341a trst_num} @var{trst}
+Set TRST GPIO number. If not specified, default D1 is used.
+@end deffn
+
+@deffn {Config Command} {ch341a srst_num} @var{srst}
+Set SRST GPIO number. If not specified, default D2 is used.
+@end deffn
